      "content": "Proponents of the bill rely on the trickle-down economic theory, which posits that corporate tax cuts will spur massive investment and job creation. This argument is based on the belief that increased corporate profits will inevitably lead to higher wages and broader economic prosperity. However, critics argue that these incentives primarily benefit shareholders and executives, leading to increased stock buybacks rather than meaningful wage growth for the middle class. The reality is that the benefits of these tax cuts are heavily debated, with evidence suggesting they disproportionately favor capital owners.",
